swL3MgmtMIB.name: swL3MgmtMIB
swL3MgmtMIB.description: The Structure of Layer 3 Network Management Information for the proprietary enterprise.

Ipv6Address.name: Ipv6Address
Ipv6Address.description: This data type is used to model IPv6 addresses. This is a binary string of 16 octets in network byte-order.

VrId.name: VrId
VrId.description: A number which, along with an interface index (ifIndex), serves to uniquely identify a virtual router on a given VRRP router. A set of one or more associated addresses is assigned to a VRID.

swL3DevCtrlRIPState.name: swL3DevCtrlRIPState
swL3DevCtrlRIPState.description: This object indicates Routing Information Protocol (RIP) version 2 function is enabled or disabled.

swL3DevCtrlOSPFState.name: swL3DevCtrlOSPFState
swL3DevCtrlOSPFState.description: This object indicates OSPF protocol is enabled or disabled.

swL3DevCtrlDVMRPState.name: swL3DevCtrlDVMRPState
swL3DevCtrlDVMRPState.description: This object indicates DVMRP protocol is enabled or disabled.

swL3DevCtrlPIMState.name: swL3DevCtrlPIMState
swL3DevCtrlPIMState.description: This object indicates PIM protocol is enabled or disabled.

swL3DevCtrlVRRPState.name: swL3DevCtrlVRRPState
swL3DevCtrlVRRPState.description: This object indicates VRRP protocol is enabled or disabled.

swL3DevCtrlVrrpPingState.name: swL3DevCtrlVrrpPingState
swL3DevCtrlVrrpPingState.description: This object indicates VRRP protocol Ping is enabled or disabled.

swL3DevCtrlDHCPAutoConfigState.name: swL3DevCtrlDHCPAutoConfigState
swL3DevCtrlDHCPAutoConfigState.description: This object indicates auto config is enabled or disabled.

swL3IpCtrlTable.name: swL3IpCtrlTable
swL3IpCtrlTable.description: This table contains IP interface information.

swL3IpCtrlEntry.name: swL3IpCtrlEntry
swL3IpCtrlEntry.description: A list of information about a specific IP interface.

swL3IpCtrlInterfaceName.name: swL3IpCtrlInterfaceName
swL3IpCtrlInterfaceName.description: This object indicates the name of the IP interface.

swL3IpCtrlIfIndex.name: swL3IpCtrlIfIndex
swL3IpCtrlIfIndex.description: This object uniquely identifies the IP interface number in the swL3IpCtrlTable.

swL3IpCtrlIpAddr.name: swL3IpCtrlIpAddr
swL3IpCtrlIpAddr.description: The IP address of the interface. This object only can take the value of the unicast IP address.

swL3IpCtrlIpSubnetMask.name: swL3IpCtrlIpSubnetMask
swL3IpCtrlIpSubnetMask.description: The IP net mask for this interface.

swL3IpCtrlVlanName.name: swL3IpCtrlVlanName
swL3IpCtrlVlanName.description: This object indicates the IP control entry's VLAN name. The VLAN name in each entry must be unique in the IP Control Table.

swL3IpCtrlProxyArp.name: swL3IpCtrlProxyArp
swL3IpCtrlProxyArp.description: This object indicates enable/disable of the proxy ARP function for IPv4.

swL3IpCtrlSecondary.name: swL3IpCtrlSecondary
swL3IpCtrlSecondary.description: When this is true(1), the IP address is the secondary IP. When false(2), the IP address is the primary IP.

swL3IpCtrlMode.name: swL3IpCtrlMode
swL3IpCtrlMode.description: This object indicates the IP operation mode. other(1) - This entry is currently in use but the conditions under which it will remain are determined by each of the following values. bootp(3) - The IP address will be set automatically from a BOOTP server. dhcp(4) - The IP address will be set automatically from a DHCP server.

swL3IpCtrlAdminState.name: swL3IpCtrlAdminState
swL3IpCtrlAdminState.description: The state of the IP interface.

swL3IpCtrlIpv6LinkLocalAddress.name: swL3IpCtrlIpv6LinkLocalAddress
swL3IpCtrlIpv6LinkLocalAddress.description: The IPv6 link local address for this interface.

swL3IpCtrlIpv6LinkLocalPrefixLen.name: swL3IpCtrlIpv6LinkLocalPrefixLen
swL3IpCtrlIpv6LinkLocalPrefixLen.description: The IPv6 prefix length for this IPv6 link local address.

swL3IpCtrlState.name: swL3IpCtrlState
swL3IpCtrlState.description: This variable displays the status of the entry. The status is used for creating, modifying, and deleting instances of the objects in this table.

swL3IpCtrlIpv6LinkLocalAutoState.name: swL3IpCtrlIpv6LinkLocalAutoState
swL3IpCtrlIpv6LinkLocalAutoState.description: The state of the IPv6 link local auto.

swL3IpCtrlLocalProxyArp.name: swL3IpCtrlLocalProxyArp
swL3IpCtrlLocalProxyArp.description: If the state is enabled, the switch will be allowed to respond to the proxy ARP proxy ARP when the source IP and destination IP are on the same interface.

swL3IpCtrlIpMtu.name: swL3IpCtrlIpMtu
swL3IpCtrlIpMtu.description: The MTU is the largest size of the IP datagram which may be transferred using a specific data link connection. The MTU value is a design parameter of a LAN and is a mutually agreed value (i.e. both ends of a link agree to use the same specific value) for most WAN links. The MTU range is based on the chip of the current device. The suggested minimum value is 1500 bytes. The suggested maximum value is the size of the jumbo frame minus 36. The suggested default setting is 1500 bytes.

swL3IpCtrlDhcpv6ClientState.name: swL3IpCtrlDhcpv6ClientState
swL3IpCtrlDhcpv6ClientState.description: The state of the Dhcpv6 Client.

swL3IpCtrlIpDirectedBroadcastState.name: swL3IpCtrlIpDirectedBroadcastState
swL3IpCtrlIpDirectedBroadcastState.description: The state of the IP Directed Broadcast.

swL3IpCtrlIpDhcpOption12State.name: swL3IpCtrlIpDhcpOption12State
swL3IpCtrlIpDhcpOption12State.description: Enable or disable insertion of option 12 in the DHCPDISCOVER and DHCPREQUEST message.

swL3IpCtrlIpDhcpOption12HostName.name: swL3IpCtrlIpDhcpOption12HostName
swL3IpCtrlIpDhcpOption12HostName.description: Specify the host name to be inserted in the DHCPDISCOVER and DHCPREQUEST message. The specified host name must start with a letter, end with a letter or digit, and have only letters, digits, and hyphen as interior characters; the maximal length is 63. By default, the host name is empty. When set an empty host name, means to clear the host name setting and use the default value to encode option 12.

swL3IpCtrlDhcpv6ClientPDState.name: swL3IpCtrlDhcpv6ClientPDState
swL3IpCtrlDhcpv6ClientPDState.description: The state of the Dhcpv6 Client PD.

swL3IpCtrlDhcpv6ClientPDPrefixName.name: swL3IpCtrlDhcpv6ClientPDPrefixName
swL3IpCtrlDhcpv6ClientPDPrefixName.description: This object indicates the name for the DHCPv6 Client PD. If the swL3IpCtrlDhcpv6ClientPDState is disabled, this object will be clear and can't write.

swL3IpCtrlDhcpv6ClientPDPrefix.name: swL3IpCtrlDhcpv6ClientPDPrefix
swL3IpCtrlDhcpv6ClientPDPrefix.description: The IPv6 prefix obtained form delegation router.

swL3IpCtrlDhcpv6ClientPDPrefixLen.name: swL3IpCtrlDhcpv6ClientPDPrefixLen
swL3IpCtrlDhcpv6ClientPDPrefixLen.description: The IPv6 prefix length for the prefix obtained from delegation router.

swL3Ipv6CtrlTable.name: swL3Ipv6CtrlTable
swL3Ipv6CtrlTable.description: This table contains IPv6 information of an IP interface.

swL3Ipv6CtrlEntry.name: swL3Ipv6CtrlEntry
swL3Ipv6CtrlEntry.description: A list of IPv6 information about a specific IP interface.

swL3Ipv6CtrlInterfaceName.name: swL3Ipv6CtrlInterfaceName
swL3Ipv6CtrlInterfaceName.description: This object indicates the name of the IP interface.

swL3Ipv6CtrlMaxReassmblySize.name: swL3Ipv6CtrlMaxReassmblySize
swL3Ipv6CtrlMaxReassmblySize.description: Maximum Reassembly Size of the IP interface.

swL3Ipv6CtrlNsRetransTimer.name: swL3Ipv6CtrlNsRetransTimer
swL3Ipv6CtrlNsRetransTimer.description: Neighbor solicitation's retransmit timer. The unit is set in milliseconds.

swL3Ipv6CtrlRaMinRtrAdvInterval.name: swL3Ipv6CtrlRaMinRtrAdvInterval
swL3Ipv6CtrlRaMinRtrAdvInterval.description: The minimum time allowed between sending unsolicited multicast Router Advertisements from the interface. The unit is set in seconds. It must be no less than 3 seconds and no greater than .75 * MaxRtrAdvInterval. Default value: 0.33 * MaxRtrAdvInterval

swL3Ipv6CtrlRaMaxRtrAdvInterval.name: swL3Ipv6CtrlRaMaxRtrAdvInterval
swL3Ipv6CtrlRaMaxRtrAdvInterval.description: The maximum time allowed between sending unsolicited multicast Router Advertisements from the interface. The unit is set in seconds.

swL3Ipv6CtrlRaLifeTime.name: swL3Ipv6CtrlRaLifeTime
swL3Ipv6CtrlRaLifeTime.description: Indicates the lifetime of the router as the default router.

swL3Ipv6CtrlRaReachableTime.name: swL3Ipv6CtrlRaReachableTime
swL3Ipv6CtrlRaReachableTime.description: Indicates the amount of time that a node can consider a neighboring node reachable after receiving a reachability confirmation.

swL3Ipv6CtrlRaRetransTime.name: swL3Ipv6CtrlRaRetransTime
swL3Ipv6CtrlRaRetransTime.description: Indicates the amount of time between retransmissions of neighbor solicited messages. The unit is set in millisecond.

swL3Ipv6CtrlRaHopLimit.name: swL3Ipv6CtrlRaHopLimit
swL3Ipv6CtrlRaHopLimit.description: Indicates the default value of the hop limit field in the IPv6 header for packets sent by hosts that receive this RA message.

swL3Ipv6CtrlRaManagedFlag.name: swL3Ipv6CtrlRaManagedFlag
swL3Ipv6CtrlRaManagedFlag.description: When enabled, it indicates that hosts receiving this RA must use a stateful address configuration protocol to obtain an address in the addition to the addresses derived from the stateless address configuration.

swL3Ipv6CtrlRaOtherConfigFlag.name: swL3Ipv6CtrlRaOtherConfigFlag
swL3Ipv6CtrlRaOtherConfigFlag.description: When enabled, it indicates that hosts receiving this RA must use a stateful address configuration protocol to obtain an on-link address configuration information.

swL3Ipv6AddressCtrlTable.name: swL3Ipv6AddressCtrlTable
swL3Ipv6AddressCtrlTable.description: This table contains IPv6 address information for each IP interface.

swL3Ipv6AddressCtrlEntry.name: swL3Ipv6AddressCtrlEntry
swL3Ipv6AddressCtrlEntry.description: A list of information about a specific IPv6 address.

swL3Ipv6AddressCtrlInterfaceName.name: swL3Ipv6AddressCtrlInterfaceName
swL3Ipv6AddressCtrlInterfaceName.description: This object indicates the name of the IP interface.

swL3Ipv6AddressCtrlPrefixLen.name: swL3Ipv6AddressCtrlPrefixLen
swL3Ipv6AddressCtrlPrefixLen.description: Indicates the prefix length of this IPv6 address.

swL3Ipv6AddressCtrlPreferredLifeTime.name: swL3Ipv6AddressCtrlPreferredLifeTime
swL3Ipv6AddressCtrlPreferredLifeTime.description: Indicates the number of seconds that an address, based on the specified prefix, using the stateless address configuration, remains in preferred state. For an infinite valid lifetime, the value can be set to 0xffffffff.

swL3Ipv6AddressCtrlValidLifeTime.name: swL3Ipv6AddressCtrlValidLifeTime
swL3Ipv6AddressCtrlValidLifeTime.description: Indicates the number of seconds that an address, based on the specified prefix, using the stateless address configuration, remains valid. For an infinite valid lifetime, the value can be set to 0xffffffff.

swL3Ipv6AddressCtrlOnLinkFlag.name: swL3Ipv6AddressCtrlOnLinkFlag
swL3Ipv6AddressCtrlOnLinkFlag.description: When enabled, the address implied by the specified prefix is available on the link where the RA message is received.

swL3Ipv6AddressCtrlAutonomousFlag.name: swL3Ipv6AddressCtrlAutonomousFlag
swL3Ipv6AddressCtrlAutonomousFlag.description: When enabled, the specified prefix will be used to create an autonomous address configuration.

swL3Ipv6AddressCtrlState.name: swL3Ipv6AddressCtrlState
swL3Ipv6AddressCtrlState.description: This variable displays the status of the entry. The status is used for creating, modifying, and deleting instances of the objects in this table.

swL3Ipv6AddressCtrlAddressType.name: swL3Ipv6AddressCtrlAddressType
swL3Ipv6AddressCtrlAddressType.description: This object indicates the type of the IPv6 address. manual(1): the IPv6 address is configured by user. dhcpv6(2): the IPv6 address is assigned by DHCPv6 server. stateless(3): the IPv6 address is assigned by router advertisement.

swL3Ipv6DHCPv6CPDAddrCtrlTable.name: swL3Ipv6DHCPv6CPDAddrCtrlTable
swL3Ipv6DHCPv6CPDAddrCtrlTable.description: This table contain the information of the IPv6 address which based on DHCPv6 client PD.

swL3Ipv6DHCPv6CPDAddrCtrlEntry.name: swL3Ipv6DHCPv6CPDAddrCtrlEntry
swL3Ipv6DHCPv6CPDAddrCtrlEntry.description: A list of information about a specific DHCPv6 Client PD IPv6 address.

swL3Ipv6DHCPv6CPDAddrCtrlInterfaceName.name: swL3Ipv6DHCPv6CPDAddrCtrlInterfaceName
swL3Ipv6DHCPv6CPDAddrCtrlInterfaceName.description: This object indicates the name of the IP interface.

swL3Ipv6DHCPv6CPDAddrCtrlPrefixName.name: swL3Ipv6DHCPv6CPDAddrCtrlPrefixName
swL3Ipv6DHCPv6CPDAddrCtrlPrefixName.description: This object indicates the name of the prefix based on which the IPv6 address will be generate.

swL3Ipv6DHCPv6CPDAddrCtrlIPv6addr.name: swL3Ipv6DHCPv6CPDAddrCtrlIPv6addr
swL3Ipv6DHCPv6CPDAddrCtrlIPv6addr.description: Specify the suffix of the IPv6 address.

swL3Ipv6DHCPv6CPDAddrCtrlPrefixLen.name: swL3Ipv6DHCPv6CPDAddrCtrlPrefixLen
swL3Ipv6DHCPv6CPDAddrCtrlPrefixLen.description: Indicates the prefix length of this IPv6 address.

swL3Ipv6DHCPv6CPDAddrCtrlState.name: swL3Ipv6DHCPv6CPDAddrCtrlState
swL3Ipv6DHCPv6CPDAddrCtrlState.description: This variable displays the status of the entry. The status is used for creating and deleting instances of the objects in this table.

swL3IpCtrlAllIpIfState.name: swL3IpCtrlAllIpIfState
swL3IpCtrlAllIpIfState.description: This object indicates all interface function state of the device.

swL3LoopBackIpCtrlTable.name: swL3LoopBackIpCtrlTable
swL3LoopBackIpCtrlTable.description: This table contains loopback IP interface information.

swL3LoopBackIpCtrlEntry.name: swL3LoopBackIpCtrlEntry
swL3LoopBackIpCtrlEntry.description: A list of information about a specific loopback IP interface.

swL3LoopBackIpCtrlInterfaceName.name: swL3LoopBackIpCtrlInterfaceName
swL3LoopBackIpCtrlInterfaceName.description: This object indicates the name of the loopback IP interface.

swL3LoopBackIpCtrlIfIndex.name: swL3LoopBackIpCtrlIfIndex
swL3LoopBackIpCtrlIfIndex.description: This object uniquely identifies the loopback IP interface number in the swL3LoopBackIpCtrlTable.

swL3LoopBackIpCtrlIpAddr.name: swL3LoopBackIpCtrlIpAddr
swL3LoopBackIpCtrlIpAddr.description: The IP address of the loopback interface. This object only can take the value of the unicast IP address.

swL3LoopBackIpCtrlIpSubnetMask.name: swL3LoopBackIpCtrlIpSubnetMask
swL3LoopBackIpCtrlIpSubnetMask.description: The IP net mask for this loopback interface.

swL3LoopBackIpCtrlAdminState.name: swL3LoopBackIpCtrlAdminState
swL3LoopBackIpCtrlAdminState.description: The state of the loopback IP interface.

swL3LoopBackIpCtrlRowStatus.name: swL3LoopBackIpCtrlRowStatus
swL3LoopBackIpCtrlRowStatus.description: This variable displays the status of the entry. The status is used for creating, modifying, and deleting instances of the objects in this table.

swL3IpFdbInfoTable.name: swL3IpFdbInfoTable
swL3IpFdbInfoTable.description: A table that contains forwarding and/or filtering information. This information is used by the switch in determining how to propagate the received IP packets.

swL3IpFdbInfoEntry.name: swL3IpFdbInfoEntry
swL3IpFdbInfoEntry.description: Information about a specific IP address for which the bridge has some forwarding and/or filtering information.

swL3IpFdbInfoIpAddr.name: swL3IpFdbInfoIpAddr
swL3IpFdbInfoIpAddr.description: A IP address for which switch has forwarding and/or filtering information.

swL3IpFdbInfoIpSubnetMask.name: swL3IpFdbInfoIpSubnetMask
swL3IpFdbInfoIpSubnetMask.description: A IP net mask for this interface for which the switch has forwarding and/or filtering information.

swL3IpFdbInfoPort.name: swL3IpFdbInfoPort
swL3IpFdbInfoPort.description: Either the value '0', or the port number of the port on which packet having a IP address equal to the value of the corresponding instance of swL3IpFdbInfoIpAddr has been seen. A value of '0' indicates that the port number has not been learned but that switch does have some forwarding/filtering information about this address.

swL3IpArpAgingTime.name: swL3IpArpAgingTime
swL3IpArpAgingTime.description: The timeout period in minutes for aging out dynamically learned ARP information.

swL3IpStaticRouteTable.name: swL3IpStaticRouteTable
swL3IpStaticRouteTable.description: This entity's IP static Routing table.

swL3IpStaticRouteEntry.name: swL3IpStaticRouteEntry
swL3IpStaticRouteEntry.description: A particular route to a particular destination, under a particular policy. Once an entry is built,it shouldn't be modified.That is,it just supports create and delete actions.

swL3IpStaticRouteDest.name: swL3IpStaticRouteDest
swL3IpStaticRouteDest.description: The destination IP address of this route. This object may not take a Multicast (Class D) address value. Any assignment (implicit or otherwise) of an instance of this object to a value x must be rejected if the bitwise logical-AND of x with the value of the corresponding instance of the swL3IpStaticRouteMask object is not equal to x.

swL3IpStaticRouteMask.name: swL3IpStaticRouteMask
swL3IpStaticRouteMask.description: Indicate the mask to be logical-AND with the destination address before being compared to the value in the swL3IpStaticRouteDest field. For those systems that do not support arbitrary subnet masks, an agent constructs the value of the swL3IpStaticRouteMask by reference to the IP Address Class. Any assignment (implicit or otherwise) of an instance of this object to a value x must be rejected if the bitwise logical-AND of x with the value of the corresponding instance of the swL3IpStaticRouteDest object is not equal to swL3IpStaticRouteDest.

swL3IpStaticRouteBkupState.name: swL3IpStaticRouteBkupState
swL3IpStaticRouteBkupState.description: The routing state for this route.The value SHOULD be primary(1), backup(2) or none(3).

swL3IpStaticRouteNextHop.name: swL3IpStaticRouteNextHop
swL3IpStaticRouteNextHop.description: Specifies the IP address for the next hop router. An IP address of 255.255.255.255 denotes a Null interface as the next hop.

swL3IpStaticRouteMetric.name: swL3IpStaticRouteMetric
swL3IpStaticRouteMetric.description: Specifies the routing metric for this route.

swL3IpStaticRouteStatus.name: swL3IpStaticRouteStatus
swL3IpStaticRouteStatus.description: This object indicates the status of this entry. other(1) - this entry is currently in use but the conditions under which it will remain so are different from each of the following values. invalid(2) - writing this value to the object, and then the corresponding entry will be removed from the table. valid(3) - this entry resides in the table. active(4) - the nextHop of this entry exists in the ARP table. inActive(5) - the next hop of this entry does not exist in the ARP table.

swL3IpStaticRouteWeight.name: swL3IpStaticRouteWeight
swL3IpStaticRouteWeight.description: Specifies the weight value. Used for the weighted multipath.

swL3IpStaticRouteInterfaceName.name: swL3IpStaticRouteInterfaceName
swL3IpStaticRouteInterfaceName.description: Specifies the name of the IP interface.

swL3RelayDhcpState.name: swL3RelayDhcpState
swL3RelayDhcpState.description: This object indicates if the DHCP Relay function is enabled or disabled.

swL3RelayDhcpHopCount.name: swL3RelayDhcpHopCount
swL3RelayDhcpHopCount.description: This object indicates the maximum number of router hops that the BOOTP packets can cross.

swL3RelayDhcpTimeThreshold.name: swL3RelayDhcpTimeThreshold
swL3RelayDhcpTimeThreshold.description: This object indicates the minimum time in seconds within which the switch must relay the DHCP request. If this time is exceeded, the switch will drop the DHCP packet.

swL3RelayDhcpCtrlTable.name: swL3RelayDhcpCtrlTable
swL3RelayDhcpCtrlTable.description: This table specifies the IP address as a destination to forward (relay) DHCP packets to.

swL3RelayDhcpCtrlEntry.name: swL3RelayDhcpCtrlEntry
swL3RelayDhcpCtrlEntry.description: A list of information specifying the IP address as a destination to forward (relay) DHCP packets to.

swL3RelayDhcpCtrlInterfaceName.name: swL3RelayDhcpCtrlInterfaceName
swL3RelayDhcpCtrlInterfaceName.description: The name of the IP interface.

swL3RelayDhcpCtrlState.name: swL3RelayDhcpCtrlState
swL3RelayDhcpCtrlState.description: This object indicates the status of this entry. other(1) - this entry is currently in use but the conditions under which it will remain so are different from each of the following values. invalid(2) - writing this value to the object, and then the corresponding entry will be removed from the table. valid(3) - this entry is reside in the table.

swL3RelayDhcpOption82State.name: swL3RelayDhcpOption82State
swL3RelayDhcpOption82State.description: This object indicates DHCP Relay Option 82 function is enabled or disabled.

swL3RelayDhcpOption82CheckState.name: swL3RelayDhcpOption82CheckState
swL3RelayDhcpOption82CheckState.description: This object indicates DHCP Relay Option 82 Check function is enabled or disabled.

swL3RelayDhcpOption82Policy.name: swL3RelayDhcpOption82Policy
swL3RelayDhcpOption82Policy.description: This object indicates DHCP Relay Option 82 Policy.

swL3DHCPRelayOption60State.name: swL3DHCPRelayOption60State
swL3DHCPRelayOption60State.description: This object indicates DHCP relay option 60 function is enabled or disabled.

swL3DHCPRelayOption60DefMode.name: swL3DHCPRelayOption60DefMode
swL3DHCPRelayOption60DefMode.description: This object indicates default mode that has no option 60 mathcing rules. relay(1): means to relay the packet to the IP address which is specified by swL3DHCPRelayOption60DefRelayIp. drop(2): means to drop the packet.

swL3DHCPRelayOption60DefTable.name: swL3DHCPRelayOption60DefTable
swL3DHCPRelayOption60DefTable.description: This table indicates the default relay servers for the packet that has no option 60 mathcing rules.

swL3DHCPRelayOption60DefEntry.name: swL3DHCPRelayOption60DefEntry
swL3DHCPRelayOption60DefEntry.description: A list of information indicates the default relay servers for the packet that has no option 60 mathcing rules.

swL3DHCPRelayOption60DefRelayIp.name: swL3DHCPRelayOption60DefRelayIp
swL3DHCPRelayOption60DefRelayIp.description: This object indicates the IP address of default relay server.

swL3DHCPRelayOption60DefRowStatus.name: swL3DHCPRelayOption60DefRowStatus
swL3DHCPRelayOption60DefRowStatus.description: This object indicates the status of this entry.

swL3DHCPRelayOption60Table.name: swL3DHCPRelayOption60Table
swL3DHCPRelayOption60Table.description: This table indicates the relay servers for the packet at option 60 rules.

swL3DHCPRelayOption60Entry.name: swL3DHCPRelayOption60Entry
swL3DHCPRelayOption60Entry.description: A list of information indicates the relay servers for the packet at option 60 rules.

swL3DHCPRelayOption60String.name: swL3DHCPRelayOption60String
swL3DHCPRelayOption60String.description: This object indicates string of this entry. Note that it is theoretically possible for a valid string to exceed the allowed length of an SNMP object identifier, and thus be impossible to represent in tables in this MIB that are indexed by string.

swL3DHCPRelayOption60RelayIp.name: swL3DHCPRelayOption60RelayIp
swL3DHCPRelayOption60RelayIp.description: This object indicates the IP address of relay server.

swL3DHCPRelayOption60MatchType.name: swL3DHCPRelayOption60MatchType
swL3DHCPRelayOption60MatchType.description: This object indicates match state of this entry. exact(1): means the option 60 string in the packet must full match with the specified string. partial(2): means the option 60 string in the packet only need partial match with the specified string.

swL3DHCPRelayOption60RowStatus.name: swL3DHCPRelayOption60RowStatus
swL3DHCPRelayOption60RowStatus.description: This object indicates the status of this entry.

swL3DHCPRelayOption61State.name: swL3DHCPRelayOption61State
swL3DHCPRelayOption61State.description: This object indicates DHCP relay option 61 function is enabled or disabled.

swL3DHCPRelayOption61DefMode.name: swL3DHCPRelayOption61DefMode
swL3DHCPRelayOption61DefMode.description: This object indicates default mode that has no option 61 mathcing rules. relay(1): means to relay the packet to the IP address which is specified by swL3DHCPRelayOption61DefRelayIp. drop(2): means to drop the packet.

swL3DHCPRelayOption61DefRelayIp.name: swL3DHCPRelayOption61DefRelayIp
swL3DHCPRelayOption61DefRelayIp.description: This object indicates the IP address of default relay server that has no option 61 mathcing rules. Pay attention to when swL3DHCPRelayOption61Mode is: relay(1): this object must be set together. drop(2): this object can not be set, and it always returns '0.0.0.0'.

swL3DHCPRelayOption61Table.name: swL3DHCPRelayOption61Table
swL3DHCPRelayOption61Table.description: This table indicates the relay servers for the packet at option 61 rules.

swL3DHCPRelayOption61Entry.name: swL3DHCPRelayOption61Entry
swL3DHCPRelayOption61Entry.description: A list of information indicates the relay servers for the packet at option 61 rules.

swL3DHCPRelayOption61ClientType.name: swL3DHCPRelayOption61ClientType
swL3DHCPRelayOption61ClientType.description: This object indicates client type of this entry. mac(1): means the client-ID which is the MAC address of client. string(2): means the client-ID which is specified string by administrator.

swL3DHCPRelayOption61ClientID.name: swL3DHCPRelayOption61ClientID
swL3DHCPRelayOption61ClientID.description: This object indicates string of this entry. When swL3DHCPRelayOption61ClientType is mac(1), the format of this object should be XX-XX-XX-XX-XX-XX (MAC address). Note that it is theoretically possible for a valid string to exceed the allowed length of an SNMP object identifier, and thus be impossible to represent in tables in this MIB that are indexed by string.

swL3DHCPRelayOption61Mode.name: swL3DHCPRelayOption61Mode
swL3DHCPRelayOption61Mode.description: This object indicates mode of this entry. relay(1): means to relay the packet to the IP address which is specified by swL3DHCPRelayOption61RelayIp. drop(2): means to drop the packet.

swL3DHCPRelayOption61RelayIp.name: swL3DHCPRelayOption61RelayIp
swL3DHCPRelayOption61RelayIp.description: This object indicates the IP address of relay server. Pay attention to when swL3DHCPRelayOption61Mode is: relay(1): this object must be set together. drop(2): this object can not be set, and it always returns '0.0.0.0'.

swL3DHCPRelayOption61RowStatus.name: swL3DHCPRelayOption61RowStatus
swL3DHCPRelayOption61RowStatus.description: This object indicates the status of this entry.

swL3RelayDnsState.name: swL3RelayDnsState
swL3RelayDnsState.description: This object indicates if the DNS Relay function is enabled or disabled.

swL3RelayDnsPrimaryServer.name: swL3RelayDnsPrimaryServer
swL3RelayDnsPrimaryServer.description: This object indicates the address of the primary DNS server.

swL3RelayDnsSecondaryServer.name: swL3RelayDnsSecondaryServer
swL3RelayDnsSecondaryServer.description: This object indicates the address of the secondary DNS server.

swL3RelayDnsCacheState.name: swL3RelayDnsCacheState
swL3RelayDnsCacheState.description: This object indicates DNS Relay cache is enabled or disabled.

swL3RelayDnsStaticTableState.name: swL3RelayDnsStaticTableState
swL3RelayDnsStaticTableState.description: This object indicates DNS Relay static table is enabled or disabled.

swL3RelayDnsCtrlTable.name: swL3RelayDnsCtrlTable
swL3RelayDnsCtrlTable.description: This table displays the current DNS relay static table.

swL3RelayDnsCtrlEntry.name: swL3RelayDnsCtrlEntry
swL3RelayDnsCtrlEntry.description: A list of information display the current DNS relay static table.

swL3RelayDnsCtrlDomainName.name: swL3RelayDnsCtrlDomainName
swL3RelayDnsCtrlDomainName.description: The domain name of the entry.

swL3RelayDnsCtrlIpAddr.name: swL3RelayDnsCtrlIpAddr
swL3RelayDnsCtrlIpAddr.description: The IP address of the entry.

swL3RelayDnsCtrlState.name: swL3RelayDnsCtrlState
swL3RelayDnsCtrlState.description: This object indicates the status of this entry. other(1) - this entry is currently in use but the conditions under which it will remain so are different from each of the following values. invalid(2) - writing this value to the object, and then the corresponding entry will be removed from the table. valid(3) - this entry is reside in the table.

swL3Md5Table.name: swL3Md5Table
swL3Md5Table.description: This table displays the current MD5 key table.

swL3Md5Entry.name: swL3Md5Entry
swL3Md5Entry.description: A list of information displays the current MD5 key table.

swL3Md5Key.name: swL3Md5Key
swL3Md5Key.description: An MD5 password of up to 16 bytes.

swL3Md5RowStatus.name: swL3Md5RowStatus
swL3Md5RowStatus.description: This object indicates the status of this entry.

swL3RouteRedistriTable.name: swL3RouteRedistriTable
swL3RouteRedistriTable.description: Route redistribution allows routers on the network that are running different routing protocols to exchange routing information. This is accomplished by comparing the routes stored in the varios routers' routing tables and assigning appropriate metrics. This information is then exchanged among the various routers according to the individual routers current routing protocol.

swL3RouteRedistriEntry.name: swL3RouteRedistriEntry
swL3RouteRedistriEntry.description: A list of information displaying the route redistribution table.

swL3RouteRedistriSrcProtocol.name: swL3RouteRedistriSrcProtocol
swL3RouteRedistriSrcProtocol.description: Allows the selection of the protocol of the source device.

swL3RouteRedistriDstProtocol.name: swL3RouteRedistriDstProtocol
swL3RouteRedistriDstProtocol.description: Allows the selection of the protocol of the destination device.

swL3RouteRedistriType.name: swL3RouteRedistriType
swL3RouteRedistriType.description: Allows the selection of one of the methods for calculating the metric value.

swL3RouteRedistriMetric.name: swL3RouteRedistriMetric
swL3RouteRedistriMetric.description: Allows the entry of an OSPF interface cost. This is analogous to a Hop Count in the RIP routing protocol. The value '0' indicates default value.

swL3RouteRedistriRowStatus.name: swL3RouteRedistriRowStatus
swL3RouteRedistriRowStatus.description: This object indicates the status of this entry.

swL3RouteRedistriRouteMapName.name: swL3RouteRedistriRouteMapName
swL3RouteRedistriRouteMapName.description: This Object just works when the destination protocol is BGP and indicate the route-map working when redistribute the route to BGP.

swL3OspfHostTable.name: swL3OspfHostTable
swL3OspfHostTable.description: The list of Hosts, and their metrics, that the router will advertise as host routes.

swL3OspfHostEntry.name: swL3OspfHostEntry
swL3OspfHostEntry.description: A metric to be advertised, for a given type of service, when a given host is reachable.

swL3OspfHostIpAddress.name: swL3OspfHostIpAddress
swL3OspfHostIpAddress.description: The IP Address of the Host.

swL3OspfHostTOS.name: swL3OspfHostTOS
swL3OspfHostTOS.description: The Type of Service of the route being configured.

swL3OspfHostAreaID.name: swL3OspfHostAreaID
swL3OspfHostAreaID.description: The Area the Host Entry is to be found within. By default, the area that a subsuming OSPF interface is in, or 0.0.0.0

swL3OspfHostStatus.name: swL3OspfHostStatus
swL3OspfHostStatus.description: This variable displays the status of the entry. Setting it to 'invalid' has the effect of rendering it inoperative. The internal effect (row removal) is implementation dependent.

swL3ospfVirtIfTable.name: swL3ospfVirtIfTable
swL3ospfVirtIfTable.reference: OSPF Version 2, Appendix C.4 Virtual link parameters
swL3ospfVirtIfTable.description: Information about this router's virtual inter- faces.

swL3ospfVirtIfEntry.name: swL3ospfVirtIfEntry
swL3ospfVirtIfEntry.description: Information about a single Virtual Interface.

swL3ospfVirtIfAreaId.name: swL3ospfVirtIfAreaId
swL3ospfVirtIfAreaId.description: The Transit Area that the Virtual Link traverses. By definition, this is not 0.0.0.0

swL3ospfVirtIfNeighbor.name: swL3ospfVirtIfNeighbor
swL3ospfVirtIfNeighbor.description: The Router ID of the Virtual Neighbor.

swL3ospfVirtIfTransitDelay.name: swL3ospfVirtIfTransitDelay
swL3ospfVirtIfTransitDelay.description: The estimated number of seconds it takes to transmit a link- state update packet over this interface.

swL3ospfVirtIfRetransInterval.name: swL3ospfVirtIfRetransInterval
swL3ospfVirtIfRetransInterval.description: The number of seconds between link-state ad- vertisement retransmissions, for adjacencies belonging to this interface. This value is also used when retransmitting database descrip- tion and link-state request packets. This value should be well over the expected round- trip time.

swL3ospfVirtIfHelloInterval.name: swL3ospfVirtIfHelloInterval
swL3ospfVirtIfHelloInterval.description: The length of time, in seconds, between the Hello packets that the router sends on the in- terface. This value must be the same for the virtual neighbor.

swL3ospfVirtIfRtrDeadInterval.name: swL3ospfVirtIfRtrDeadInterval
swL3ospfVirtIfRtrDeadInterval.description: The number of seconds that a router's Hello packets have not been seen before it's neigh- bors declare the router down. This should be some multiple of the Hello interval. This value must be the same for the virtual neigh- bor.

swL3ospfVirtIfEvents.name: swL3ospfVirtIfEvents
swL3ospfVirtIfEvents.description: The number of state changes or error events on this Virtual Link

swL3ospfVirtIfAuthType.name: swL3ospfVirtIfAuthType
swL3ospfVirtIfAuthType.description: The authentication type specified for a virtu- al interface. Additional authentication types may be assigned locally.

swL3ospfVirtIfAuthKey.name: swL3ospfVirtIfAuthKey
swL3ospfVirtIfAuthKey.reference: OSPF Version 2, Section 9 The Interface Data Structure
swL3ospfVirtIfAuthKey.description: If Authentication Type is simplePassword, the device will left adjust and zero fill to 8 oc- tets. Note that unauthenticated interfaces need no authentication key, and simple password authen- tication cannot use a key of more than 8 oc- tets. Larger keys are useful only with authen- tication mechanisms not specified in this docu- ment.

swL3ospfVirtIfStatus.name: swL3ospfVirtIfStatus
swL3ospfVirtIfStatus.description: This variable displays the status of the en- try. Setting it to 'invalid' has the effect of rendering it inoperative. The internal effect (row removal) is implementation dependent.

swL3ospfIfTable.name: swL3ospfIfTable
swL3ospfIfTable.reference: OSPF Version 2, Appendix C.3 Router interface parameters
swL3ospfIfTable.description: The OSPF Interface Table describes the inter- faces from the viewpoint of OSPF.

swL3ospfIfEntry.name: swL3ospfIfEntry
swL3ospfIfEntry.description: The OSPF Interface Entry describes one inter- face from the viewpoint of OSPF.

swL3ospfIfIpAddress.name: swL3ospfIfIpAddress
swL3ospfIfIpAddress.description: The IP address of this OSPF interface.

swL3ospfAddressLessIf.name: swL3ospfAddressLessIf
swL3ospfAddressLessIf.description: For the purpose of easing the instancing of addressed and addressless interfaces; This variable takes the value 0 on interfaces with IP Addresses, and the corresponding value of ifIndex for interfaces having no IP Address.

swL3ospfIfAreaId.name: swL3ospfIfAreaId
swL3ospfIfAreaId.description: A 32-bit integer uniquely identifying the area to which the interface connects. Area ID 0.0.0.0 is used for the OSPF backbone.

swL3ospfIfType.name: swL3ospfIfType
swL3ospfIfType.description: The OSPF interface type. By way of a default, this field may be intuited from the corresponding value of ifType. Broad- cast LANs, such as Ethernet and IEEE 802.5, take the value 'broadcast', X.25 and similar technologies take the value 'nbma', and links that are definitively point to point take the value 'pointToPoint'.

swL3ospfIfAdminStat.name: swL3ospfIfAdminStat
swL3ospfIfAdminStat.description: The OSPF interface's administrative status. The value formed on the interface, and the in- terface will be advertised as an internal route to some area. The value 'disabled' denotes that the interface is external to OSPF.

swL3ospfIfRtrPriority.name: swL3ospfIfRtrPriority
swL3ospfIfRtrPriority.description: The priority of this interface. Used in multi-access networks, this field is used in the designated router election algorithm. The value 0 signifies that the router is not eligi- ble to become the designated router on this particular network. In the event of a tie in this value, routers will use their Router ID as a tie breaker.

swL3ospfIfTransitDelay.name: swL3ospfIfTransitDelay
swL3ospfIfTransitDelay.description: The estimated number of seconds it takes to transmit a link state update packet over this interface.

swL3ospfIfRetransInterval.name: swL3ospfIfRetransInterval
swL3ospfIfRetransInterval.description: The number of seconds between link-state ad- vertisement retransmissions, for adjacencies belonging to this interface. This value is also used when retransmitting database descrip- tion and link-state request packets.

swL3ospfIfHelloInterval.name: swL3ospfIfHelloInterval
swL3ospfIfHelloInterval.description: The length of time, in seconds, between the Hello packets that the router sends on the in- terface. This value must be the same for all routers attached to a common network.

swL3ospfIfRtrDeadInterval.name: swL3ospfIfRtrDeadInterval
swL3ospfIfRtrDeadInterval.description: The number of seconds that a router's Hello packets have not been seen before it's neigh- bors declare the router down. This should be some multiple of the Hello interval. This value must be the same for all routers attached to a common network.

swL3ospfIfPollInterval.name: swL3ospfIfPollInterval
swL3ospfIfPollInterval.description: The larger time interval, in seconds, between the Hello packets sent to an inactive non- broadcast multi- access neighbor.

swL3ospfIfDesignatedRouter.name: swL3ospfIfDesignatedRouter
swL3ospfIfDesignatedRouter.description: The IP Address of the Designated Router.

swL3ospfIfBackupDesignatedRouter.name: swL3ospfIfBackupDesignatedRouter
swL3ospfIfBackupDesignatedRouter.description: The IP Address of the Backup Designated Router.

swL3ospfIfEvents.name: swL3ospfIfEvents
swL3ospfIfEvents.description: The number of times this OSPF interface has changed its state, or an error has occurred.

swL3ospfIfMulticastForwarding.name: swL3ospfIfMulticastForwarding
swL3ospfIfMulticastForwarding.description: The way multicasts should forwarded on this interface; not forwarded, forwarded as data link multicasts, or forwarded as data link uni- casts. Data link multicasting is not meaning- ful on point to point and NBMA interfaces, and setting ospfMulticastForwarding to 0 effective- ly disables all multicast forwarding.

swL3ospfIfDemand.name: swL3ospfIfDemand
swL3ospfIfDemand.description: Indicates whether Demand OSPF procedures (hel- lo supression to FULL neighbors and setting the DoNotAge flag on proogated LSAs) should be per- formed on this interface.

swL3ospfIfAuthType.name: swL3ospfIfAuthType
swL3ospfIfAuthType.description: The authentication type specified for an in- terface. Additional authentication types may be assigned locally.

swL3ospfIfAuthKey.name: swL3ospfIfAuthKey
swL3ospfIfAuthKey.reference: OSPF Version 2, Section 9 The Interface Data Structure
swL3ospfIfAuthKey.description: The Authentication Key. If the Area's Author- ization Type is simplePassword, and the key length is shorter than 8 octets, the agent will left adjust and zero fill to 8 octets. Note that unauthenticated interfaces need no authentication key, and simple password authen- tication cannot use a key of more than 8 oc- tets. Larger keys are useful only with authen- tication mechanisms not specified in this docu- ment. When read, ospfIfAuthKey always returns an Oc- tet String of length zero.

swL3ospfIfPassiveMode.name: swL3ospfIfPassiveMode
swL3ospfIfPassiveMode.description: Assign the designated entry to be a passive interface.

swL3ospfIfDistributeListInType.name: swL3ospfIfDistributeListInType
swL3ospfIfDistributeListInType.description: The type of route filter for distribute list in.

swL3ospfIfDistributeListInName.name: swL3ospfIfDistributeListInName
swL3ospfIfDistributeListInName.description: The name of route filter for distribute list in.

swL3RoutePreferenceRIP.name: swL3RoutePreferenceRIP
swL3RoutePreferenceRIP.description: Used to configure the route preference of RIP.

swL3RoutePreferenceOSPFIntra.name: swL3RoutePreferenceOSPFIntra
swL3RoutePreferenceOSPFIntra.description: Used to configure the route preference of OSPF Intra.

swL3RoutePreferenceStatic.name: swL3RoutePreferenceStatic
swL3RoutePreferenceStatic.description: Used to configure the route preference of Static.

swL3RoutePreferenceLocal.name: swL3RoutePreferenceLocal
swL3RoutePreferenceLocal.description: Used to read the route preference of Local.

swL3RoutePreferenceOSPFInter.name: swL3RoutePreferenceOSPFInter
swL3RoutePreferenceOSPFInter.description: Used to configure the route preference of OSPF Inter.

swL3RoutePreferenceOSPFExtT1.name: swL3RoutePreferenceOSPFExtT1
swL3RoutePreferenceOSPFExtT1.description: Used to configure the route preference of OSPFExtT1.

swL3RoutePreferenceOSPFExtT2.name: swL3RoutePreferenceOSPFExtT2
swL3RoutePreferenceOSPFExtT2.description: Used to configure the route preference of OSPF ExtT2.

swL3RoutePreferenceDefault.name: swL3RoutePreferenceDefault
swL3RoutePreferenceDefault.description: Used to configure the route preference of Default route.

swL3RoutePreferenceEBGP.name: swL3RoutePreferenceEBGP
swL3RoutePreferenceEBGP.description: Used to configure the route preference of EBGP.

swL3RoutePreferenceIBGP.name: swL3RoutePreferenceIBGP
swL3RoutePreferenceIBGP.description: Used to configure the route preference of IBGP.

swL3ospfAreaTable.name: swL3ospfAreaTable
swL3ospfAreaTable.reference: OSPF Version 2, Section 6 The Area Data Struc- ture
swL3ospfAreaTable.description: Information describing the configured parame- ters and cumulative statistics of the router's attached areas.

swL3ospfAreaEntry.name: swL3ospfAreaEntry
swL3ospfAreaEntry.description: Information describing the configured parame- ters and cumulative statistics of one of the router's attached areas.

swL3ospfAreaId.name: swL3ospfAreaId
swL3ospfAreaId.description: A 32-bit integer uniquely identifying an area. Area ID 0.0.0.0 is used for the OSPF backbone.

swL3ospfAreaType.name: swL3ospfAreaType
swL3ospfAreaType.description: The type specified for an area.

swL3ospfAreaSummaryState.name: swL3ospfAreaSummaryState
swL3ospfAreaSummaryState.description: Whether the summary LSA is effective for this area.

swL3ospfAreaMetric.name: swL3ospfAreaMetric
swL3ospfAreaMetric.description: Enter the metric (1 - 65535; 0 for auto cost) of this area.

swL3ospfAreaStatus.name: swL3ospfAreaStatus
swL3ospfAreaStatus.description: This variable displays the status of the en- try. Setting it to 'invalid' has the effect of rendering it inoperative. The internal effect (row removal) is implementation dependent.

swL3dvmrpInterfaceTable.name: swL3dvmrpInterfaceTable
swL3dvmrpInterfaceTable.description: The (conceptual) table listing the router's multicast- capable interfaces.

swL3dvmrpInterfaceEntry.name: swL3dvmrpInterfaceEntry
swL3dvmrpInterfaceEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the dvmrpInterfaceTable. This row augments ipMRouteInterfaceEntry in the IP Multicast MIB, where the threshold object resides.

swL3dvmrpInterfaceIfIndex.name: swL3dvmrpInterfaceIfIndex
swL3dvmrpInterfaceIfIndex.description: The ifIndex value of the interface for which DVMRP is enabled.

swL3dvmrpInterfaceLocalAddress.name: swL3dvmrpInterfaceLocalAddress
swL3dvmrpInterfaceLocalAddress.description: The IP address this system will use as a source address on this interface. On unnumbered interfaces, it must be the same value as dvmrpInterfaceLocalAddress for some interface on the system.

swL3dvmrpInterfaceMetric.name: swL3dvmrpInterfaceMetric
swL3dvmrpInterfaceMetric.description: The distance metric for this interface which is used to calculate distance vectors.

swL3dvmrpInterfaceNbrTimeout.name: swL3dvmrpInterfaceNbrTimeout
swL3dvmrpInterfaceNbrTimeout.description: Used to set the timer before neighbors are timed out.

swL3dvmrpInterfaceStatus.name: swL3dvmrpInterfaceStatus
swL3dvmrpInterfaceStatus.description: The status of this entry. Creating the entry enables DVMRP on the virtual interface; destroying the entry or setting it to notInService disables DVMRP on the virtual interface.

swL3dvmrpInterfaceRcvBadPkts.name: swL3dvmrpInterfaceRcvBadPkts
swL3dvmrpInterfaceRcvBadPkts.description: The number of DVMRP packets received on the interface by the DVMRP process which were subsequently discarded as invalid (e.g. invalid packet format, or a route report from an unknown neighbor).

swL3dvmrpInterfaceRcvBadRoutes.name: swL3dvmrpInterfaceRcvBadRoutes
swL3dvmrpInterfaceRcvBadRoutes.description: The number of routes, in valid DVMRP packets, which were ignored because the entry was invalid.

swL3OspfInternalLsdbTable.name: swL3OspfInternalLsdbTable
swL3OspfInternalLsdbTable.reference: OSPF Version 2, Section 12 Link State Adver- tisements
swL3OspfInternalLsdbTable.description: The OSPF Process's Link State Database.

swL3OspfInternalLsdbAreaId.name: swL3OspfInternalLsdbAreaId
swL3OspfInternalLsdbAreaId.description: The 32 bit identifier of the Area from which the LSA was received.

swL3OspfInternalLsdbType.name: swL3OspfInternalLsdbType
swL3OspfInternalLsdbType.description: The type of the link state advertisement. Each link state type has a separate advertise- ment format.

swL3OspfInternalLsdbLsid.name: swL3OspfInternalLsdbLsid
swL3OspfInternalLsdbLsid.description: The Link State ID is an LS Type Specific field containing either a Router ID or an IP Address; it identifies the piece of the routing domain that is being described by the advertisement.

swL3OspfInternalLsdbRouterId.name: swL3OspfInternalLsdbRouterId
swL3OspfInternalLsdbRouterId.description: The 32 bit number that uniquely identifies the originating router in the Autonomous System.

swL3OspfInternalLsdbMetric.name: swL3OspfInternalLsdbMetric
swL3OspfInternalLsdbMetric.description: Enter the metric (1 - 65535; 0 for auto cost) of this area.

swL3OspfInternalLsdbSequenceNo.name: swL3OspfInternalLsdbSequenceNo
swL3OspfInternalLsdbSequenceNo.description: The sequence number field is a signed 32-bit integer. It is used to detect old and dupli- cate link state advertisements. The space of sequence numbers is linearly ordered. The larger the sequence number the more recent the advertisement.

swL3OspfInternalLsdbAge.name: swL3OspfInternalLsdbAge
swL3OspfInternalLsdbAge.description: This field is the age of the link state adver- tisement in seconds.

swL3OspfInternalLsdbChecksum.name: swL3OspfInternalLsdbChecksum
swL3OspfInternalLsdbChecksum.description: This field is the checksum of the complete contents of the advertisement, excepting the age field. The age field is excepted so that an advertisement's age can be incremented without updating the checksum. The checksum used is the same that is used for ISO connec- tionless datagrams; it is commonly referred to as the Fletcher checksum.

swL3OspfExternalLsdbTable.name: swL3OspfExternalLsdbTable
swL3OspfExternalLsdbTable.description: The OSPF Process's Links State Database.

swL3OspfExternalLsdbType.name: swL3OspfExternalLsdbType
swL3OspfExternalLsdbType.description: The type of the link state advertisement. Each link state type has a separate advertise- ment format.

swL3OspfExternalLsdbLsid.name: swL3OspfExternalLsdbLsid
swL3OspfExternalLsdbLsid.description: The Link State ID is an LS Type Specific field containing either a Router ID or an IP Address; it identifies the piece of the routing domain that is being described by the advertisement.

swL3OspfExternalLsdbRouterId.name: swL3OspfExternalLsdbRouterId
swL3OspfExternalLsdbRouterId.description: The 32 bit number that uniquely identifies the originating router in the Autonomous System.

swL3OspfExternalLsdbMetric.name: swL3OspfExternalLsdbMetric
swL3OspfExternalLsdbMetric.description: Enter the metric (1 - 65535; 0 for auto cost) of this area.

swL3OspfExternalLsdbMetricType.name: swL3OspfExternalLsdbMetricType
swL3OspfExternalLsdbMetricType.description: Enter the metric type of this area.

swL3OspfExternalLsdbSequenceNo.name: swL3OspfExternalLsdbSequenceNo
swL3OspfExternalLsdbSequenceNo.description: The sequence number field is a signed 32-bit integer. It is used to detect old and dupli- cate link state advertisements. The space of sequence numbers is linearly ordered. The larger the sequence number the more recent the advertisement.

swL3OspfExternalLsdbAge.name: swL3OspfExternalLsdbAge
swL3OspfExternalLsdbAge.description: This field is the age of the link state adver- tisement in seconds.

swL3OspfExternalLsdbChecksum.name: swL3OspfExternalLsdbChecksum
swL3OspfExternalLsdbChecksum.description: This field is the checksum of the complete contents of the advertisement, except the age field. The age field is the exception so that an advertisement's age can be incremented without updating the checksum. The checksum used is the same that is used for ISO connec- tionless datagrams; it is commonly referred to as the Fletcher checksum.

swL3OspfExternalLsdbForwardingAddress.name: swL3OspfExternalLsdbForwardingAddress
swL3OspfExternalLsdbForwardingAddress.description: This field is the forwarding address.

swL3OspfExternalLsdbRouteTag.name: swL3OspfExternalLsdbRouteTag
swL3OspfExternalLsdbRouteTag.description: This field is the route tag.

swL3VrrpOperTable.name: swL3VrrpOperTable
swL3VrrpOperTable.description: Operations table for a VRRP router which consists of a sequence (i.e., one or more conceptual rows) of 'swL3vrrpOperEntry' items.

swL3VrrpOperEntry.name: swL3VrrpOperEntry
swL3VrrpOperEntry.description: An entry in the vrrpOperTable containing the operational characteristics of a virtual router. On a VRRP router, a given virtual router is identified by a combination of the IF index and VRID. Rows in the table cannot be modified unless the value of `swL3VrrpOperAdminState' is `disabled' and the `swL3VrrpOperState' has transitioned to `initialize'.

swL3VrrpOperIfIndex.name: swL3VrrpOperIfIndex
swL3VrrpOperIfIndex.description: The ifIndex value of the interface for which VRRP is enabled.

swL3VrrpOperVrId.name: swL3VrrpOperVrId
swL3VrrpOperVrId.description: This object contains the Virtual Router Identifier (VRID).

swL3VrrpOperVirtualMacAddr.name: swL3VrrpOperVirtualMacAddr
swL3VrrpOperVirtualMacAddr.description: The virtual MAC address of the virtual router. Although this object can be derived from the 'swL3VrrpOperVrId' object, it is defined so that it is easily obtainable by a management application and can be included in VRRP-related SNMP traps.

swL3VrrpOperState.name: swL3VrrpOperState
swL3VrrpOperState.description: The current state of the virtual router. This object has three defined values: - `initialize', which indicates that all the virtual router is waiting for a startup event. - `backup', which indicates the virtual router is monitoring the availability of the master router. - `master', which indicates that the virtual router is forwarding packets for IP addresses that are associated with this router. Setting the `swL3VrrpOperAdminState' object (below) initiates transitions in the value of this object.

swL3VrrpOperAdminState.name: swL3VrrpOperAdminState
swL3VrrpOperAdminState.description: This object will enable/disable the virtual router function. Setting the value to `up', will transition the state of the virtual router from `initialize' to `backup' or `master', depending on the value of `swL3VrrpOperPriority'. Setting the value to `down', will transition the router from `master' or `backup' to `initialize'. State transitions may not be immediate; they sometimes depend on other factors, such as the interface (IF) state. The `swL3VrrpOperAdminState' object must be set to `down' prior to modifying the other read-create objects in the conceptual row. The value of the `swL3VrrpOperRowStatus' object (below) must be `active', signifying that the conceptual row is valid (i.e., the objects are correctly set), in order for this object to be set to `up'.

swL3VrrpOperPriority.name: swL3VrrpOperPriority
swL3VrrpOperPriority.description: This object specifies the priority to be used for the virtual router master election process. Higher values imply higher priority. A priority of '0', although not settable, is sent by the master router to indicate that this router has ceased to participate in VRRP and a backup virtual router should transition to become a new master. A priority of 255 is used for the router that owns the associated IP address(es).

swL3VrrpOperMasterIpAddr.name: swL3VrrpOperMasterIpAddr
swL3VrrpOperMasterIpAddr.description: The master router's real (primary) IP address. This is the IP address listed as the source in VRRP advertisement last received by this virtual router.

swL3VrrpOperCriticalIpAddr.name: swL3VrrpOperCriticalIpAddr
swL3VrrpOperCriticalIpAddr.description: In the case where there is more than one IP address for a given `ifIndex', this object is used to specify the IP address that will become the `swL3VrrpOperMasterIpAddr', should the virtual router transition from backup to master. If this object is set to 0.0.0.0, the IP address which is numerically lowest will be selected.

swL3VrrpOperAuthType.name: swL3VrrpOperAuthType
swL3VrrpOperAuthType.description: Authentication type used for VRRP protocol exchanges between virtual routers. This value of this object is the same for a given ifIndex. New enumerations to this list can only be added via a new RFC on the standards track.

swL3VrrpOperAuthKey.name: swL3VrrpOperAuthKey
swL3VrrpOperAuthKey.description: The Authentication Key. This object is set according to the value of the 'swL3VrrpOperAuthType' object ('simpleTextPassword' or 'ipAuthenticationHeader'). If the length of the value is less than 16 octets, the agent will left adjust and zero fill to 16 octets. The value of this object is the same for a given ifIndex. When read, swL3VrrpOperAuthKey always returns an Octet String of length zero.

swL3VrrpOperAdvertisementInterval.name: swL3VrrpOperAdvertisementInterval
swL3VrrpOperAdvertisementInterval.description: The time interval, in seconds, between sending advertisement messages. Only the master router sends VRRP advertisements.

swL3VrrpOperPreemptMode.name: swL3VrrpOperPreemptMode
swL3VrrpOperPreemptMode.description: Controls whether a higher priority virtual router will preempt a lower priority master.

swL3VrrpOperVirtualRouterUpTime.name: swL3VrrpOperVirtualRouterUpTime
swL3VrrpOperVirtualRouterUpTime.description: This is the value of the `sysUpTime' object when this virtual router (i.e., the `swL3VrrpOperState') transitioned out of `initialized'.

swL3VrrpOperVirtualIpAddr.name: swL3VrrpOperVirtualIpAddr
swL3VrrpOperVirtualIpAddr.description: The assigned IP addresses that a virtual router is responsible for backing up.

swL3VrrpOperRowStatus.name: swL3VrrpOperRowStatus
swL3VrrpOperRowStatus.description: The row status variable, used in accordance to installation and removal conventions for conceptual rows. The rowstatus of a currently active row in the vrrpOperTable is constrained by the operational state of the corresponding virtual router. When `vrrpOperRowStatus' is set to active(1), no other objects in the conceptual row, with the exception of `swL3VrrpOperAdminState', can be modified. Prior to setting the `swL3VrrpOperRowStatus' object from `active' to a different value, the `swL3VrrpOperAdminState' object must be set to `down' and the `vrrpOperState' object be transitioned to `initialize'. To create a row in this table, a manager sets this object to either createAndGo(4) or createAndWait(5). Until instances of all corresponding columns are appropriately configured, the value of the corresponding instance of the `vrrpOperRowStatus' column will be read as notReady(3). In particular, a newly created row cannot be made active(1) until (minimally) the corresponding instance of `swL3VrrpOperVrId' has been set and there is at least one active row in the `swL3VrrpAssoIpAddrTable' defining an associated IP address for the virtual router.

swL3IpMcastStaticRouteTable.name: swL3IpMcastStaticRouteTable
swL3IpMcastStaticRouteTable.description: IP multicast static routing allows you to have multicast paths diverge from the unicast paths.

swL3IpMcastStaticRouteEntry.name: swL3IpMcastStaticRouteEntry
swL3IpMcastStaticRouteEntry.description: A list of information about IP multicast static routes.

swL3IpMcastStaticRouteIpmrouteAddr.name: swL3IpMcastStaticRouteIpmrouteAddr
swL3IpMcastStaticRouteIpmrouteAddr.description: If the source IP address of the received IP multicast packet matches this Ipmrouteaddress, the RPF network is used to do an RPF check.

swL3IpMcastStaticRouteIpmrouteMask.name: swL3IpMcastStaticRouteIpmrouteMask
swL3IpMcastStaticRouteIpmrouteMask.description: This specifies an IP net Mask for this interface.

swL3IpMcastStaticRouteRpfAddr.name: swL3IpMcastStaticRouteRpfAddr
swL3IpMcastStaticRouteRpfAddr.description: If the source IP address of the received IP multicast packet matches the Ipmrouteaddress, the Rpfaddress will be used to check whether the packet received is from a legal interface. If it is set to null, it means that if the source IP address in the received IP multicast packet matches the Ipmrouteaddress, the RPF check will fail.

swL3IpMcastStaticRouteRowStatus.name: swL3IpMcastStaticRouteRowStatus
swL3IpMcastStaticRouteRowStatus.description: This object indicates the status of this entry.

swL3OspfECMPIpDestination.name: swL3OspfECMPIpDestination
swL3OspfECMPIpDestination.description: If set to 'enabled (1)', the ECMP algorithm will include the destination IP.

swL3OspfECMPIpSource.name: swL3OspfECMPIpSource
swL3OspfECMPIpSource.description: If set to 'enabled (1)', the ECMP algorithm will include the lower 5 bits of the source IP. This attribution is mutually exclusive with crc_low and crc_high. If set to 'enabled (1)', crc_low and crc_high will be excluded.

swL3OspfECMPCrcLow.name: swL3OspfECMPCrcLow
swL3OspfECMPCrcLow.description: If set to 'enabled (1)', the ECMP algorithm will include the lower 5 bits of the CRC. This attribution is mutually exclusive with crc_high and ip_source. If set to 'enabled (1)', crc_high and ip_source will be excluded.

swL3OspfECMPCrcHigh.name: swL3OspfECMPCrcHigh
swL3OspfECMPCrcHigh.description: If set to 'enabled (1)', the ECMP algorithm will include the upper 5 bits of the CRC. This attribution is mutually exclusive with ip_source and crc_low. If set to 'enabled (1)', crc_low and ip_source will be excluded.

swL3OspfECMPTCPorUDPport.name: swL3OspfECMPTCPorUDPport
swL3OspfECMPTCPorUDPport.description: If set to 'enabled (1)', the ECMP algorithm will include the TCP or UDP port.

swL3OspfECMPState.name: swL3OspfECMPState
swL3OspfECMPState.description: This object indicates the state of the OSPF ECMP function.

swL3RIPInboundRouteFilterTable.name: swL3RIPInboundRouteFilterTable
swL3RIPInboundRouteFilterTable.description: The list of inbound route filter on RIP interfaces.

swL3RIPInboundRouteFilterEntry.name: swL3RIPInboundRouteFilterEntry
swL3RIPInboundRouteFilterEntry.description: The information of inbound route filter on RIP interfaces.

swL3RIPInboundRouteFilterIfIpAddress.name: swL3RIPInboundRouteFilterIfIpAddress
swL3RIPInboundRouteFilterIfIpAddress.description: The IP Address of the RIP interface.

swL3RIPInboundRouteFilterType.name: swL3RIPInboundRouteFilterType
swL3RIPInboundRouteFilterType.description: The type of inbound route filter for the RIP interface.

swL3RIPInboundRouteFilterName.name: swL3RIPInboundRouteFilterName
swL3RIPInboundRouteFilterName.description: The name of inbound route filter for the RIP interface.

swL3Route6RedistriTable.name: swL3Route6RedistriTable
swL3Route6RedistriTable.description: IPv6 Route redistribution allows routers on the network that are running different routing protocols to exchange routing information. This is accomplished by comparing the routes stored in the varios routers' routing tables and assigning appropriate metrics. This information is then exchanged among the various routers according to the individual routers current routing protocol.

swL3Route6RedistriEntry.name: swL3Route6RedistriEntry
swL3Route6RedistriEntry.description: A list of information displaying the IPv6 route redistribution table.

swL3Route6RedistriSrcProtocol.name: swL3Route6RedistriSrcProtocol
swL3Route6RedistriSrcProtocol.description: Allows the selection of the protocol of the source device.

swL3Route6RedistriDstProtocol.name: swL3Route6RedistriDstProtocol
swL3Route6RedistriDstProtocol.description: Allows the selection of the protocol of the destination device.

swL3Route6RedistriType.name: swL3Route6RedistriType
swL3Route6RedistriType.description: Allows the selection of one of the methods for calculating the metric value.

swL3Route6RedistriMetric.name: swL3Route6RedistriMetric
swL3Route6RedistriMetric.description: Allows the entry of an OSPFv3 interface cost. This is analogous to a Hop Count in the RIPng routing protocol. The value '0' indicates default value.

swL3Route6RedistriRowStatus.name: swL3Route6RedistriRowStatus
swL3Route6RedistriRowStatus.description: This object indicates the status of this entry.
